{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"My search is always to find ways to chronicle,"},{"time":5000,"text":"to share and to document stories about people, just everyday people."},{"time":10000,"text":"Stories that offer transformation, that lean into transcendence,"},{"time":15000,"text":"but that are never sentimental,"},{"time":17000,"text":"that never look away from the darkest things about us."},{"time":21000,"text":"Because I really believe that we're never more beautiful"},{"time":24000,"text":"than when we're most ugly."},{"time":26000,"text":"Because that's really the moment we really know what we're made of."},{"time":30000,"text":"As Chris said, I grew up in Nigeria"},{"time":35000,"text":"with a whole generation -- in the '80s --"},{"time":37000,"text":"of students who were protesting a military dictatorship, which has finally ended."},{"time":43000,"text":"So it wasn't just me, there was a whole generation of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45000,"text":"But what I've come to learn"},{"time":48000,"text":"is that the world is never saved in grand messianic gestures,"},{"time":52000,"text":"but in the simple accumulation of gentle, soft, almost invisible acts of compassion,"},{"time":59000,"text":"everyday acts of compassion."},{"time":61000,"text":"In South Africa, they have a phrase called Ubuntu."},{"time":68000,"text":"Ubuntu comes out of a philosophy that says,"},{"time":70000,"text":"the only way for me to be human is for you to reflect"},{"time":74000,"text":"my humanity back at me."},{"time":76000,"text":"But if you're like me, my humanity is more like a window."},{"time":80000,"text":"I don't really see it, I don't pay attention to it"},{"time":82000,"text":"until there's, you know, like a bug that's dead on the window."},{"time":85000,"text":"Then suddenly I see it, and usually, it's never good."},{"time":89000,"text":"It's usually when I'm cussing in traffic"},{"time":92000,"text":"at someone who is trying to drive their car and drink coffee"},{"time":95000,"text":"and send emails and make notes."},{"time":99000,"text":"So what Ubuntu really says"},{"time":102000,"text":"is that there is no way for us to be human without other people."},{"time":107000,"text":"It's really very simple, but really very complicated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110000,"text":"So, I thought I should start with some stories."},{"time":113000,"text":"I should tell you some stories about remarkable people,"},{"time":115000,"text":"so I thought I'd start with my mother."},{"time":118000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":119000,"text":"And she was dark, too."},{"time":121000,"text":"My mother was English."},{"time":122000,"text":"My parents met in Oxford in the '50s,"},{"time":124000,"text":"and my mother moved to Nigeria and lived there."},{"time":126000,"text":"She was five foot two, very feisty and very English."},{"time":130000,"text":"This is how English my mother is -- or was, she just passed."},{"time":133000,"text":"She came out to California, to Los Angeles, to visit me,"},{"time":137000,"text":"and we went to Malibu, which she thought was very disappointing."},{"time":139000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":141000,"text":"And then we went to a fish restaurant,"},{"time":143000,"text":"and we had Chad, the surfer dude, serving us,"},{"time":146000,"text":"and he came up and my mother said,"},{"time":148000,"text":"\"Do you have any specials, young man?\""},{"time":150000,"text":"And Chad says, \"Sure, like, we have this, like, salmon,"},{"time":154000,"text":"that's, like, rolled in this, like, wasabi, like, crust."},{"time":156000,"text":"It's totally rad.\""},{"time":158000,"text":"And my mother turned to me and said,"},{"time":161000,"text":"\"What language is he speaking?\""},{"time":163000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":164000,"text":"I said, \"English, mum.\""},{"time":166000,"text":"And she shook her head and said,"},{"time":168000,"text":"\"Oh, these Americans. We gave them a language,"},{"time":170000,"text":"why don't they use it?\""},{"time":172000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":178000,"text":"So, this woman, who converted from the Church of England"},{"time":182000,"text":"to Catholicism when she married my father --"},{"time":184000,"text":"and there's no one more rabid than a Catholic convert --"},{"time":188000,"text":"decided to teach in the rural areas in Nigeria,"},{"time":192000,"text":"particularly among Igbo women,"},{"time":194000,"text":"the Billings ovulation method,"},{"time":196000,"text":"which was the only approved birth control by the Catholic Church."},{"time":200000,"text":"But her Igbo wasn't too good."},{"time":204000,"text":"So she took me along to translate."},{"time":206000,"text":"I was seven."},{"time":208000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":209000,"text":"So, here are these women,"},{"time":211000,"text":"who never discuss their period with their husbands,"},{"time":214000,"text":"and here I am telling them, \"Well, how often do you get your period?\""},{"time":218000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":219000,"text":"And, \"Do you notice any discharges?\""},{"time":221000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":222000,"text":"And, \"How swollen is your vulva?\""},{"time":224000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":229000,"text":"She never would have thought of herself as a feminist,"},{"time":232000,"text":"my mother, but she always used to say,"},{"time":235000,"text":"\"Anything a man can do, I can fix.\""},{"time":238000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":245000,"text":"And when my father complained about this situation,"},{"time":250000,"text":"where she's taking a seven-year-old boy"},{"time":252000,"text":"to teach this birth control, you know,"},{"time":254000,"text":"he used to say, \"Oh, you're turning him into --"},{"time":256000,"text":"you're teaching him how to be a woman.\""},{"time":258000,"text":"My mother said, \"Someone has to.\""},{"time":260000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":261000,"text":"This woman -- during the Biafran war,"},{"time":265000,"text":"we were caught in the war."},{"time":267000,"text":"It was my mother with five little children."},{"time":270000,"text":"It takes her one year, through refugee camp after refugee camp,"},{"time":273000,"text":"to make her way to an airstrip where we can fly out of the country."},{"time":275000,"text":"At every single refugee camp, she has to face off soldiers"},{"time":281000,"text":"who want to take my elder brother Mark, who was nine,"},{"time":283000,"text":"and make him a boy soldier."},{"time":285000,"text":"Can you imagine this five-foot-two woman,"},{"time":287000,"text":"standing up to men with guns who want to kill us?"},{"time":291000,"text":"All through that one year,"},{"time":293000,"text":"my mother never cried one time, not once."},{"time":296000,"text":"But when we were in Lisbon, in the airport,"},{"time":298000,"text":"about to fly to England,"},{"time":300000,"text":"this woman saw my mother wearing this dress,"},{"time":303000,"text":"which had been washed so many times it was basically see through,"},{"time":307000,"text":"with five really hungry-looking kids,"},{"time":310000,"text":"came over and asked her what had happened."},{"time":312000,"text":"And she told this woman."},{"time":313000,"text":"And so this woman emptied out her suitcase"},{"time":315000,"text":"and gave all of her clothes to my mother, and to us,"},{"time":318000,"text":"and the toys of her kids, who didn't like that very much, but --"},{"time":321000,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":322000,"text":"that was the only time she cried."},{"time":325000,"text":"And I remember years later, I was writing about my mother,"},{"time":327000,"text":"and I asked her, \"Why did you cry then?\""},{"time":329000,"text":"And she said, \"You know, you can steel your heart"},{"time":332000,"text":"against any kind of trouble, any kind of horror."},{"time":335000,"text":"But the simple act of kindness from a complete stranger"},{"time":340000,"text":"will unstitch you.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":346000,"text":"The old women in my father's village, after this war had happened,"},{"time":350000,"text":"memorized the names of every dead person,"},{"time":353000,"text":"and they would sing these dirges, made up of these names."},{"time":360000,"text":"Dirges so melancholic that they would scorch you."},{"time":362000,"text":"And they would sing them only when they planted the rice,"},{"time":366000,"text":"as though they were seeding the hearts of the dead"},{"time":368000,"text":"into the rice."},{"time":370000,"text":"But when it came for harvest time,"},{"time":372000,"text":"they would sing these joyful songs,"},{"time":374000,"text":"that were made up of the names of every child"},{"time":376000,"text":"who had been born that year."},{"time":379000,"text":"And then the next planting season, when they sang the dirge,"},{"time":383000,"text":"they would remove as many names of the dead"},{"time":386000,"text":"that equaled as many people that were born."},{"time":388000,"text":"And in this way, these women enacted a lot of transformation,"},{"time":394000,"text":"beautiful transformation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396000,"text":"Did you know, that before the genocide in Rwanda,"},{"time":400000,"text":"the word for rape and the word for marriage"},{"time":403000,"text":"was the same one?"},{"time":406000,"text":"But today, women are rebuilding Rwanda."},{"time":410000,"text":"Did you also know that after apartheid,"},{"time":413000,"text":"when the new government went into the parliament houses,"},{"time":415000,"text":"there were no female toilets in the building?"},{"time":419000,"text":"Which would seem to suggest that apartheid"},{"time":421000,"text":"was entirely the business of men."},{"time":424000,"text":"All of this to say, that despite the horror, and despite the death,"},{"time":428000,"text":"women are never really counted."},{"time":431000,"text":"Their humanity never seems to matter very much to us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":436000,"text":"When I was growing up in Nigeria --"},{"time":439000,"text":"and I shouldn't say Nigeria, because that's too general,"},{"time":441000,"text":"but in Afikpo, the Igbo part of the country where I'm from --"},{"time":444000,"text":"there were always rites of passage for young men."},{"time":447000,"text":"Men were taught to be men in the ways in which we are not women,"},{"time":451000,"text":"that's essentially what it is."},{"time":453000,"text":"And a lot of rituals involved killing, killing little animals,"},{"time":457000,"text":"progressing along, so when I turned 13 --"},{"time":459000,"text":"and, I mean, it made sense, it was an agrarian community,"},{"time":462000,"text":"somebody had to kill the animals,"},{"time":464000,"text":"there was no Whole Foods you could go and get kangaroo steak at --"},{"time":467000,"text":"so when I turned 13, it was my turn now to kill a goat."},{"time":472000,"text":"And I was this weird, sensitive kid, who couldn't really do it,"},{"time":476000,"text":"but I had to do it."},{"time":478000,"text":"And I was supposed to do this alone."},{"time":480000,"text":"But a friend of mine, called Emmanuel,"},{"time":482000,"text":"who was significantly older than me,"},{"time":484000,"text":"who'd been a boy soldier during the Biafran war,"},{"time":486000,"text":"decided to come with me."},{"time":489000,"text":"Which sort of made me feel good,"},{"time":492000,"text":"because he'd seen a lot of things."},{"time":494000,"text":"Now, when I was growing up, he used to tell me"},{"time":496000,"text":"stories about how he used to bayonet people,"},{"time":498000,"text":"and their intestines would fall out, but they would keep running."},{"time":501000,"text":"So, this guy comes with me."},{"time":504000,"text":"And I don't know if you've ever heard a goat, or seen one --"},{"time":507000,"text":"they sound like human beings,"},{"time":509000,"text":"that's why we call tragedies \"a song of a goat.\""},{"time":512000,"text":"My friend Brad Kessler says that we didn't become human"},{"time":517000,"text":"until we started keeping goats."},{"time":519000,"text":"Anyway, a goat's eyes are like a child's eyes."},{"time":524000,"text":"So when I tried to kill this goat and I couldn't,"},{"time":526000,"text":"Emmanuel bent down, he puts his hand over the mouth of the goat,"},{"time":531000,"text":"covers its eyes, so I don't have to look into them,"},{"time":534000,"text":"while I kill the goat."},{"time":537000,"text":"It didn't seem like a lot, for this guy who'd seen so much,"},{"time":541000,"text":"and to whom the killing of a goat must have seemed"},{"time":543000,"text":"such a quotidian experience,"},{"time":545000,"text":"still found it in himself to try to protect me."},{"time":551000,"text":"I was a wimp."},{"time":553000,"text":"I cried for a very long time."},{"time":555000,"text":"And afterwards, he didn't say a word."},{"time":557000,"text":"He just sat there watching me cry for an hour."},{"time":559000,"text":"And then afterwards he said to me,"},{"time":561000,"text":"\"It will always be difficult, but if you cry like this every time,"},{"time":566000,"text":"you will die of heartbreak."},{"time":568000,"text":"Just know that it is enough sometimes"},{"time":571000,"text":"to know that it is difficult.\""},{"time":576000,"text":"Of course, talking about goats makes me think of sheep,"},{"time":579000,"text":"and not in good ways."},{"time":581000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":583000,"text":"So, I was born two days after Christmas."},{"time":587000,"text":"So growing up, you know, I had a cake and everything,"},{"time":590000,"text":"but I never got any presents, because, born two days after Christmas."},{"time":595000,"text":"So, I was about nine, and my uncle had just come back from Germany,"},{"time":598000,"text":"and we had the Catholic priest over,"},{"time":601000,"text":"my mother was entertaining him with tea."},{"time":603000,"text":"And my uncle suddenly says, \"Where are Chris' presents?\""},{"time":607000,"text":"And my mother said, \"Don't talk about that in front of guests.\""},{"time":611000,"text":"But he was desperate to show that he'd just come back,"},{"time":614000,"text":"so he summoned me up, and he said,"},{"time":616000,"text":"\"Go into the bedroom, my bedroom."},{"time":618000,"text":"Take anything you want out of the suitcase."},{"time":620000,"text":"It's your birthday present.\""},{"time":622000,"text":"I'm sure he thought I'd take a book or a shirt,"},{"time":624000,"text":"but I found an inflatable sheep."},{"time":627000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":633000,"text":"So, I blew it up and ran into the living room,"},{"time":635000,"text":"my finger where it shouldn't have been,"},{"time":637000,"text":"I was waving this buzzing sheep around,"},{"time":640000,"text":"and my mother looked like she was going to die of shock."},{"time":643000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":646000,"text":"And Father McGetrick was completely unflustered,"},{"time":649000,"text":"just stirred his tea and looked at my mother and said,"},{"time":651000,"text":"\"It's all right Daphne, I'm Scottish.\""},{"time":654000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":656000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":670000,"text":"My last days in prison, the last 18 months,"},{"time":676000,"text":"my cellmate -- for the last year, the first year of the last 18 months --"},{"time":680000,"text":"my cellmate was 14 years old."},{"time":683000,"text":"The name was John James,"},{"time":686000,"text":"and in those days, if a family member committed a crime,"},{"time":690000,"text":"the military would hold you as ransom"},{"time":693000,"text":"till your family turned themselves in."},{"time":695000,"text":"So, here was this 14-year-old kid on death row."},{"time":698000,"text":"And not everybody on death row was a political prisoner."},{"time":700000,"text":"There were some really bad people there."},{"time":703000,"text":"And he had smuggled in two comics, two comic books --"},{"time":706000,"text":"\"Spiderman\" and \"X-Men.\""},{"time":708000,"text":"He was obsessed."},{"time":709000,"text":"And when he got tired of reading them,"},{"time":711000,"text":"he started to teach the men in death row how to read,"},{"time":715000,"text":"with these comic books."},{"time":717000,"text":"And so, I remember night after night,"},{"time":721000,"text":"you'd hear all these men, these really hardened criminals,"},{"time":723000,"text":"huddled around John James, reciting, \"Take that, Spidey!\""},{"time":728000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":730000,"text":"It's incredible."},{"time":733000,"text":"I was really worried."},{"time":735000,"text":"He didn't know what death row meant."},{"time":737000,"text":"I'd been there twice,"},{"time":739000,"text":"and I was terribly afraid that I was going to die."},{"time":741000,"text":"And he would always laugh, and say,"},{"time":743000,"text":"\"Come on, man, we'll make it out.\""},{"time":745000,"text":"Then I'd say, \"How do you know?\""},{"time":747000,"text":"And he said, \"Oh, I heard it on the grapevine.\""},{"time":751000,"text":"They killed him."},{"time":753000,"text":"They handcuffed him to a chair,"},{"time":756000,"text":"and they tacked his penis to a table with a six-inch nail,"},{"time":762000,"text":"then left him there to bleed to death."},{"time":765000,"text":"That's how I ended up in solitary, because I let my feelings be known."},{"time":774000,"text":"All around us, everywhere, there are people like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":779000,"text":"The Igbo used to say that they built their own gods."},{"time":785000,"text":"They would come together as a community,"},{"time":787000,"text":"and they would express a wish."},{"time":790000,"text":"And their wish would then be brought to a priest,"},{"time":792000,"text":"who would find a ritual object,"},{"time":795000,"text":"and the appropriate sacrifices would be made,"},{"time":797000,"text":"and the shrine would be built for the god."},{"time":800000,"text":"But if the god became unruly and began to ask for human sacrifice,"},{"time":805000,"text":"the Igbos would destroy the god."},{"time":807000,"text":"They would knock down the shrine,"},{"time":810000,"text":"and they would stop saying the god's name."},{"time":812000,"text":"This is how they came to reclaim their humanity."},{"time":817000,"text":"Every day, all of us here,"},{"time":819000,"text":"we're building gods that have gone rampant,"},{"time":822000,"text":"and it's time we started knocking them down"},{"time":825000,"text":"and forgetting their names."},{"time":828000,"text":"It doesn't require a tremendous thing."},{"time":831000,"text":"All it requires is to recognize among us, every day --"},{"time":835000,"text":"the few of us that can see -- are surrounded by people"},{"time":838000,"text":"like the ones I've told you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":841000,"text":"There are some of you in this room, amazing people,"},{"time":844000,"text":"who offer all of us the mirror to our own humanity."},{"time":850000,"text":"I want to end with a poem by an American poet called Lucille Clifton."},{"time":855000,"text":"The poem is called \"Libation,\" and it's for my friend Vusi"},{"time":860000,"text":"who is in the audience here somewhere."},{"time":864000,"text":"\"Libation,"},{"time":866000,"text":"North Carolina, 1999."},{"time":869000,"text":"I offer to this ground, this gin."},{"time":876000,"text":"I imagine an old man crying here,"},{"time":879000,"text":"out of the sight of the overseer."},{"time":883000,"text":"He pushes his tongue through a hole"},{"time":886000,"text":"where his tooth would be, if he were whole."},{"time":891000,"text":"It aches in that space where his tooth would be,"},{"time":895000,"text":"where his land would be,"},{"time":898000,"text":"his house, his wife, his son, his beautiful daughter."},{"time":904000,"text":"He wipes sorrow from his face,"},{"time":909000,"text":"and puts his thirsty finger to his thirsty tongue,"},{"time":913000,"text":"and tastes the salt."},{"time":919000,"text":"I call a name that could be his."},{"time":921000,"text":"This is for you, old man."},{"time":926000,"text":"This gin, this salty earth.\""},{"time":930000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":932000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}